<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="363" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,1869]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1052,1077]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is dedicated to Michail Alexeevich Kozlov (
<number box="[1081,1212,1052,1077]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="1971.0" valueMax="2006.0" valueMin="1936.0">
<date box="[1081,1212,1052,1077]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="1936" valueMax="2006">1936–2006</date>
</number>
), an entomological supervisor and frequent participant in the Soviet-Mongolian Complex Biological Expeditions 
<number box="[1258,1387,1087,1112]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="1974.5" valueMax="1982.0" valueMin="1967.0">
<date box="[1258,1387,1087,1112]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="1967" valueMax="1982">1967–1982</date>
</number>
. He collected numerous new insects in 
<collectingCountry box="[542,654,1124,1149]" name="Mongolia" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
, including the present new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="363" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,1869]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1159,1184]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">Discussion.</emphasis>
Previously, two very small 
<taxonomicName box="[654,746,1159,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[654,746,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">Hylaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species were known from the territory of 
<collectingCountry box="[1232,1345,1159,1184]" name="Mongolia" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
. One of them, 
<taxonomicName authority="Morawitz" authorityName="Morawitz" box="[228,527,1196,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="przewalskyi">
<emphasis box="[228,401,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">H. przewalskyi</emphasis>
Morawitz
</taxonomicName>
, is conspicuous because of its rich yellow coloration and is thereby easily recognised; the other, 
<taxonomicName authority="Warncke" authorityName="Warncke" box="[398,636,1231,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblitus">
<emphasis box="[398,508,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">H. oblitus</emphasis>
(Warncke)
</taxonomicName>
, is black and inconspicuous. The species was originally described as 
<taxonomicName authority="Morawitz" authorityName="Morawitz" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">H. pusillus</emphasis>
Morawitz
</taxonomicName>
(♂) und 
<taxonomicName authority="Morawitz" authorityName="Morawitz" box="[467,728,1268,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albitarsis">
<emphasis box="[467,487,1269,1292]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[504,610,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">albitarsis</emphasis>
Morawitz
</taxonomicName>
(♀), although even the author himself (
<bibRefCitation author="Morawitz" box="[1191,1428,1268,1293]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" refString="Morawitz, F. (1890) Insecta a cl. G. N. Potanin in China et in Mongolia novissime lecta. XIV. Hymenoptera Aculeata. (II). III. Apidae. Horae Societatis Entomologicae Rossicae, 24 (3 / 4), 349 - 385." type="journal article" year="1890">
Morawitz 
<number box="[1311,1371,1268,1292]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="1890.0">1890</number>
: 
<number box="[1385,1428,1268,1292]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="380.0">380</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) discussed a possible synonymy. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dathe" box="[512,729,1303,1328]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" refString="Dathe, H. H. (1986 a) Die Bienengattung Hylaeus Fabricius in der Mongolei (Hymenoptera, Colletidae). Annales historiconaturales Musei nationalis Hungarici, 78, 265 - 300." type="journal article" year="1986" yearSuffix="a">
Dathe (
<number box="[594,654,1303,1328]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="1986.0">1986</number>
a: 
<number box="[678,721,1303,1328]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="285.0">285</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
had also already pointed this out, without being able to reach a taxonomic decision. He also illustrated 
<taxonomicName authority="Warncke" authorityName="Warncke" box="[614,856,1340,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblitus">
<emphasis box="[614,728,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">H. oblitus</emphasis>
(Warncke)
</taxonomicName>
(p. 
<number box="[909,954,1340,1364]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="284.0">284</number>
, Figs 
<number box="[1028,1056,1340,1364]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="42.0">42</number>
and 
<number box="[1119,1149,1340,1364]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="43.0">43</number>
, as &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Warncke" authorityName="Warncke" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuliginosus">
<emphasis box="[1210,1436,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">Hylaeus fuliginosus</emphasis>
(Warncke)
</taxonomicName>
&quot;).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,1869]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">
Based on the specimens before us, including historical material, it is now possible to argue strongly for the separation of a further small species, 
<taxonomicName box="[594,711,1447,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kozlovi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[594,711,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">H. kozlovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[723,787,1449,1472]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
This is extraordinarily similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1189,1303,1447,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblitus">
<emphasis box="[1189,1303,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">H. oblitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in habitus, coloration and sculpture: the females even both have white tarsi. The differences are subtle, only being clearer in the proportions of the facial structures. Both species seem, where they occur, to appear in large numbers, so that usually series of specimens are available that in direct comparison can be readily assigned to the correct taxon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,1869]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">
At one of the collection localities, Elkhon 
<quantity box="[701,776,1591,1616]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" unit="km" value="25.0">25 km</quantity>
S Altai, Kozlov found on 
<date box="[1096,1284,1592,1616]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="1980-06-22" valueMax="1980-06-23" valueMin="1980-06-22">
<number box="[1096,1127,1592,1616]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="22.0">22</number>
.– 
<number box="[1147,1177,1592,1616]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="23.0">23</number>
.VI. 
<number box="[1228,1284,1592,1616]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="1980.0">1980</number>
</date>
both species directly side by side. It could easily be suspected that morphs of the same species are involved, as for example occurs in halictids. However, social structures are unknown in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1020,1112,1663,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1020,1112,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">Hylaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Only in a single case, the Brazilian 
<taxonomicName authority="Schrottky" authorityName="Schrottky" box="[260,733,1700,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor" subGenus="Hylaeopsis">
<emphasis box="[260,352,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">Hylaeus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[369,493,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">Hylaeopsis</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[510,595,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">tricolor</emphasis>
(Schrottky)
</taxonomicName>
, is &quot;facultative quasisociality&quot; suspected (
<bibRefCitation author="Sakagami" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" refString="Sakagami, S. F. &amp; Zucchi, R. (1978) Nests of Hylaeus (Hylaeopsis) tricolor: the first record of non-solitary life in colletid bees, with notes on communal and quasi-social colonies (Hymenoptera: Colletidae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 51, 597 - 614." type="journal article" year="1978">
Sakagami &amp; Zucchi, 
<number box="[151,211,1736,1760]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="1978.0">1978</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The lack of observed overlap in morphological characters also speaks against the two 'forms' being conspecific. Some characters, such as the white spot on the scape of females of 
<taxonomicName box="[1064,1179,1772,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kozlovi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1064,1179,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">H. kozlovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1188,1250,1773,1796]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, are confined to this 'form', so that despite their great similarity, we assume that two separate species are involved. In 
<figureCitation box="[1282,1386,1807,1832]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[212,1401,222,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[212,1402,207,1890]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hylaeus (Hylaeus) kozlovi sp. n., holotypus male: a — face, b — mesonotum, c — mesopleuron, d — propodeum and basal terga. Scale bar 1 mm. FIGURE 6. Hylaeus (Hylaeus) oblitus (Warncke), male: a — face, b — mesonotum, c — mesopleuron, d — propodeum and basal terga." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256902/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="363">
Figures 
<number box="[1373,1386,1807,1832]" pageId="12" pageNumber="363" value="7.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
–10, main features of the species are juxtaposed.
</paragraph>
